latestIgtvVideos.title: Yesterday.Today.Everyday
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Follow our new project page @yesterday.today.everyday to be on the same page with us ❤️❤️❤️

‘Yesterday, Today and Everyday’ is a year long timeline of events that will be created and put together by the members of the transgender community across India.

By diving deep into their culture and traditional practices, we examine their spaces of innovation, the places of their history and create new spaces by transforming this knowledge into art. This is to also say that several people from the community have always been artists in their own ways. We use our projects/collaborations as an opportunity to showcase this through cultural exchanges, shared experiences and genuine empathy building. Our work is done with mutual understanding and by sharing these stories through different mediums.

THIS PROJECT IS SUPPORTED BY KHOJ INTERNATIONAL ARTISTS' ASSOCIATION.

@khojstudios

latestIgtvVideos.title: Aravani Art Project for Facebook Art Department
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Aravani Art Project is a group of transgender artists and allies based in Bangalore, India. The Project’s mission is to foster creative connections between the global transgender community and others, with the aim of increasing trans visibility and social integration.

The group’s mural at FBHQ in Menlo Park, California originated with discussions with members of the transgender community in Bangalore around ideas of belonging and non-belonging to one's own body. The central phrase “gender free” speaks to the idea of being able to define oneself outside of cultural and societal norms. It evokes a world in which we don't need to categorize people in order to understand and empathise with them.

Thank you @fbair for the gorgeous opportunity and truly blessed to have attended the Trans & Pride march in 2018 from where it all began <3  @chandrahosur @priyankadivaakar @sadh.press @poornimatravellingsukumar <3 Happy #pride ya'll <3
#fbairprogram #aravaniartproject

#RedefiningSuccess 

In collaboration with the @aravaniartproject , we are deeply exploring identity and perception with 30 young people from our Thriving Centre. Last week, they created self-portraits, reflecting how they see themselves and want to be seen. This week’s theatre-based activities helped them explore self in relation to others, diving into themes like teamwork, communication, diversity and confidence. We celebrated creativity, curiosity and shared storytelling, reminding us that success is shaped as much by our relationships as by individual journeys. Thank you @sharanya.ramprakash for facilitating this.

Join the movement and share your own definitions using #RedefiningSuccess and tag us!

#WhatIsSuccess #YoungPeople #Theatre #Creativity #Community #Art 

@vijimsw582 @shivusairam @pavi0.7 @26ameera20 @suchitha.balasubramaniam @writeon_saba @i_prasanna_h @dyanaista Krupa, @ak_rao99 @nandinirajaramanathan @poornimatravellingsukumar @sharanya.ramprakash @gomurugan39 @hamsa_sriram @deepakharini

Art as expression. Art as joy. Art as healing.
At Poorna Santhe, the Aravani Art Project brought people together — children, families, strangers — to paint a shared story of inclusion, identity, and belonging.

This community painting was more than just colour on canvas — it was conversation, courage, and connection.

🎥 Captured & edited by Deepak Chinappa. 
Thank you, Deepak, for being with us - and for capturing these moments so they can live on forever 🌈

✨🌈 Peep into the celebration of Mes del Orgullo 2025 which came alive at #InstitutoCervantesNewDelhi in collaboration with the @embespindia with a powerful celebration of art, identity, and resistance, uniting queer voices from Spain and India. 🇪🇸🇮🇳

 Throughout June, as part of Queer Connection Spain-India cultural programme, we conducted various events such as:
🎨  A powerful and inspiring creation of mural in our exhibition hall by the artists of @aravaniartproject that you can visit until September!
🎧 A talk with @aravaniartproject , a dialogue on cross-cultural expression, and a boundary-breaking DJ set by @baby_nabi_nabi .
📚 Dissident Comic: A bold panel discussion of comic artists who draw pride, protest, and queerness into every panel.
🎬 #MostraFire!! A LGBTQIA+ Short Films: Stories that moved us, challenged us, and sparked vibrant discussion in our Cineforum.

This June, we didn’t just celebrate Pride — we amplified it. 💥
#LoveIsLove and #ArtIsPride, always.

🙏 Special thanks to our associated partners: @mostrafire @naz_foundation @thequeermuslimproject

Join us for a vital conversation exploring practical approaches to cultivating spaces where everyone feels a sense of belonging and every voice is heard, especially those impacted by disability and economic disadvantage.
Discover how inclusive design, powerful storytelling, and grassroots initiatives can drive lasting community impact. In this panel, experts and artists will share their experiences and the challenges they've faced – and continue to face – in their work to create more inclusive public spaces for all members of our community.

A year ago, Aravani Art transformed our Hejje walls into a living story of pride, identity, and belonging.

At Hejje, we believe healing begins with dignity, for every body, every journey, every voice.

This Pride Month, we honour the colours that continue to speak of love, inclusion, and strength. 🌈

[Pride Month, Inclusion, Health, Healthcare, Pride]

#Msr #MsrHealth

As Pride Month draws to a close, a shoutout to @vinnimaheshwari25 and @karnikabai, two amazing artists from the @aravaniartproject, who spent a week with us last summer, covering our cafe in a gorgeous mural. We fondly remember their week here, not just for the life and colour they brought to our space but also for all the shared meals, the conversations, the playing with the dogs, the forest walks, way they opened space for our staff to paint along with them and learn from them about art, about gender, about inclusion. Special thanks to @poornimatravellingsukumar for facilitating their stay with us and designing the mural!
